observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to:
a. Require every Concerned Officials to prepare a Disbursement Voucher in accordance with Section 44 - Chapter 3 of Volume 1 of NGAS Manual for Local Government Units;
b. Require the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer and Other Concerned Officials to strictly comply with the requirements of Section 344 of R.A. No. 7160 and Section 32 of The New Government Accounting System (NGAS) Manual for Local Government Units.

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Accountant direct the concerned accounting personnel to maintain subsidiary ledger cards for each group of PPEs;

The Supply and Property Unit maintain the equivalent Property Card for PPE to account for the receipt and disposition of the same;

The Inventory Committee prepare a consolidated report of physical count for each group of PPEs using the prescribed formats in the GAM for LGUs; and

The Municipal Accountant reconcile PPE items in the reports of physical count for each group of PPEs with the accounting records, then, effect necessary adjustments to ensure fair presentation of the PPE accounts in the financial statements.

